One of the best tower defense games out there, & I've played literally hundreds & have ludicrously high standards.  This game (& it's sequel, Myth Defense 2: Dark Forces) have fantastic graphics, good selection of towers, good UI, lots of persistent upgrades, open maps, enemy intelligence increasing with hardness level, an interactive menu with all the towers & enemies, & their unique addition to the TD genre; alchemy/runes. Both games rank up there with my gold standard of TD games: Fieldrunners 2.  That said, I personally think this game is actually superior to the sequel. More balanced set of towers (as there is less of an emphasis on enemy type), more persistent upgrades, more runes, & NO FROST MAGES (you'll understand if you play the sequel).  The only real negative is it can get repetitive/tedious later on. The higher hardness levels have an incredibly high number of waves, but playing on a lower difficulty becomes too easy & gives negligible glory points.  Overall, great game, though; still easily one of my favorites.
